,Not Recommended,396160,25102389,"Posted: 23 August, 2016",all,Sobou,"Autumn 2015. Steam sale. Bundle of RPG Maker games for $2. 4 games, $0.50 each. I said sure, why not, how bad could it be? What is the Secret of Magia?It's a lie. It's a farce. It's a buggy, broken, terribly developed, messy piece of junk that should not be on Steam. Yet somehow it is. And if just playing the game wasn't enough, digging into these Steam reviews is even more eye-opening than one would think.When the dev himself is complaining about the publisher messing up his game, screwing it up, and even trying to hide that IT is the publisher (Epic Quest Games), you know something is foul.But if finding all those solid negative reviews and reading them isn't enough, have some more with this one.Action RPG? Yes, but only barely. Inspired by great games? Possibly, but this is so barebones and by the book that it hardly echoes of any of them mentioned on the Store page. Huge world? Nonsense. It's small enough to be easily beaten in less than 3 hours, AND you even have the in-game maps found to prove it. Tyranny of an evil, supernatural dictator? More like an ambiguous bird being who wakes you up and threatens your life if you don't gather plot items (as seen in one of the screenshots).I mean honestly the entire ""About This Game"" bit can be properly summarized down to ""Secret of Magia is an action RPG. Your story begins in a town. As you venture out, you'll earn levels and find obvious dungeons that have broken weapons. You start weak, you'll get strong, and you will never need to go back to your starting village. Explore a tiny world, grind aimlessly on cheap monsters, and go beat up the final boss.""4 side-quests of a moderately ambiguous nature. A really tiny overworld. Practically no plot whatsoever beyond ""go find the four things"". Flatter, more two dimensional characters than paper. Enemies that level with you, a battle system that is easily broken, weapon crafting and item drops that serve no real solid purpose. And a final boss who upon defeat compliments you then kicks you back to the title screen. That same final boss is the one who kick starts the plot to begin with, and that's basically all the plot you get.Secret of Magia is ONLY worth the cards it drops, and even then how much can you make? This is better off lost and forgotten about, tossed into the proverbial rubbish as it is now. Do not repeat my mistake.Because honestly, even fifty cents worth of candy gives more enjoyment than Secret of Magia."
