76561198035662759,Not Recommended,396160,33114302,Posted: 1 July,all,jwrfb26,"Secret of Magia is a curiosity in that it's a wonder it made it onto Steam at all.  It obviously has a lot of ideas going into it, but none are brought to fruition and little of the game feels finished or satisfying as a result.  The game features weapon crafting, but the weapons you make are useless compared to what you can buy by the time you can craft them.  It features potion crafting which requires gathering items from defeated monsters.  However, defeating monsters means gaining levels and gaining levels is more of a drawback than a plus.  You rarely feel that your character is getting stronger since monsters level up with him and they get stronger faster.  The game has side quests, only five in total, and not all of them give rewards.  Money is too easy to come by, so you might as well spend it all on potions and armor to make the game more bearable.This is not the kind of game that you pay for and I'm sorry that I did, even though it was on a massive sale.  This is the kind of game that someone puts on the Internet for free so he can get feedback about what to do betterin his next project.  This is an amateur's first attempt at an action RPG and the creator must have a heck of a lot of audacity to think he can sell this.  Don't make the mistake that I did.  Don't buy it.  It's not worth the few hours it will take to play through.  At least, it's not worth money."
