,Not Recommended,396160,20574865,"Posted: 16 January, 2016",all,Vaagur,"Secret of Magia is an ARPG made in RPGmaker. It is not like other RPGmaker game, as it is not turn-based... It's more of an action game.The pathing of monsters and their attacks are quite frustating to play against, some just dash to you in zigzag kinda patterns and are almost impossible to dodge. On the other hand, with anything but a dagger or a bow, you can sit next to monsters and kill them to your side. With a bow, you can just kill them from afar without them trying to kill you.It could have been a great game, but there are too many flaws. Mana regen is slow, leveling-up actually makes the monsters harder to kill overall. Classes are a little meaningless and have no really specific skills. There's also no abilities to unlock as you gain levels.There's no maps, so you have to keep the layout of the map in your head and the game is just pretty, bland... In the first 2 dungeons anyways, all you have to do is kill the unique monster inside the zone, get his key and then unlock the door that leads to the boss room, that's not very original!The music is not too bad, but I heard it wasn't composed for this game, so I won't praise it too much. The graphics are fair enough for RPGmaker, but they could be way better. There are some game breaking bugs (just pressing f12 for example, it crashes your game). The game is also very short.The game is really cheap, about $1, but even there, it's not a game I would really recommend playing. If you are a fan of RPGmaker games, then maybe this is for you, otherwise, I did not enjoy it very much, it is a bit too clunky and unfun to play."
