,Recommended,396160,32032771,Posted: 28 May,all,YPRPG,"Secret Of Magia is an action RPG with a hack and slash combat system and approximately 3 hours worth of gameplay.The world map contains a sequence of areas which lead away from your home town, with enemies becoming more difficult, the further you go. Levelling up is pointless as enemies level up with you, but the further flung enemies have fancier moves that make them more formidable. The map is open world, and you can easily retrace your steps.The main mission consists of capturing the souls of four different bosses, then defeating the final boss. To get to each of the bosses, you must enter a cave, then find and defeat a powerful enemy which holds a key to the door where the boss is found. Defeating that boss will reveal its soul.There are several areas and towns to explore, and a handful of quests to complete. There is enough content here that it's possible to make it through the first two hours, without ever realizing that you've overlooked the main mission.As for the main mission, it is not well explained at all, being only vaguely hinted at by some of the NPCs. The only way you'd know what to look for, is if you read up on the game beforehand, or stumble across the key by randomly killing the enemy that drops it.The story is virtually non-existent, as the side quests are given in the most blunt way possible, and the ending is equally lacking in fanfare.There is extensive customization of your character in terms of class, equipment, magic, and craftable items; however, this is largely wasted, because most of it is unnecessary to beat the game, and you can easily earn enough gold through combat to buy the strongest equipment in the shop, and more potions than you'll ever need.This game has a little bit of action and a little bit of adventure, but probably not enough of either one individually to satisfy its prospective fans. The hack and slash gameplay might prove too easy for its hardcare fans, while for adventure RPG enthusiasts, the story is somewhat lacking. There are five achievements, however, which are relatively easy to accomplish, if you prefer something more basic."
