,Not Recommended,396160,24025860,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,renmeechum,"I bought this game from a quad pack of rpg maker games.  The pack cost me I believe a dollar for all 4 games.  Even with the fact this game was 25 cents.  The loss of time I could have been playing other games makes it not worth it.1. Leveling doesn't matter. - All creatures level with you, be it the starting rats, or bosses.  They give more xp and more gold every time you level and go to a new screen.  This removes the element of leveling altogether really and frankly I don't understand why you level in this game, other than the fact the maker knows leveling is important some how.2. Story line might exist? - The story line is so lackluster that you could argue there isn't one.  I would argue there isn't one.  This is the best I could come up with for storyline ""I wake/call on your soul to kill the 4 elemental gods and bring them to me""  That is it, there are 5 quests otherwise that sort of vaguely lead you towards your goal and only the frostfire dagger quest is interesting in my opinion.3. Combat is terrible - There are multiple classes and I chose the paladin since I thought it would be neat to block.  There is no block animation and I saw no reason to do it ever.  The cooldown on enemy attacks is so low that the time it takes to block, recover your ""stamina"" to swing makes it so that NO monster makes it viable.  By the end of the game I was killing every creature the exact same as I started with. stand slightly to the left of it and use a weapon with a wider arc then just ahead of me.  This killed everything in the game by just spamming attack.In all honesty I think this was someones first attempt at making a game and for a groundwork attempt its not terrible, however, this should not have been released for public use.  It just lacks everything in every category.  You can see where the ideas got laid down and the creator has potential if they can flesh out the game and do their own thing.However this game is SO bad, NO ONE has written a guide. No one thought the game had enough depth or importance to write how to beat it.  That is how bad it is.  Even if you get this game for free, even if you receive it accidently as part of a pack.Do Not Waste Your Time.Spend your free time doing anything else like watch paint dry.  Or you know play an actually good game."
