,Not Recommended,396160,20127859,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,Ekima,"I wanted to like this game, but it's simply making it too hard. For the price, it's not too bad - but it has some serious flaws. If you're looking for something to kill a bit of time, it's fine, but I feel like it could have been so much more.Pros:It's a cute little game overall, it has an interesting battle system, which I definitely like, however, that's about all it has going for it. The different attacks of the monsters gives an interesting challenge.Cons:Although there are occasionally some nice graphics, the overall mapping is rather dull. Every house has the same layout and almost the same interior, the outside is rather lifeless.The story and characters seem one-dimensional and without any purpose.Possibly most glaring, there's a huge balancing problem. The monsters' combat abilities scale with your level, and it doesn't do it very well.Other than that there are a lot of obvious glitches that should have been fixed by now. It's really a shame, because the game does have some potential."
