,Recommended,396160,30127392,Posted: 23 February,all,Rapxtor,"Secret of Magia is RPG with a very short story behind it and very few quest to do, it offer a kind of clunky combat since there is a main attack, a skill and a guard if you have your shield equipped, but you can only attack in four directions, like up/down or left/right, doesnt let you do  diagonal attacks, wich make the gameplay wierd and its worst to avoid enemies that way since you are always align with them to do damage.You are free to explore the world and take up quests, the ones you find off course, bc there isnt any kind of information related to that, nor the game give you any tips, you have to talk with every body to find out, the leveling is fast and fluid, but at some point is kind of annoying while doing quests bc as moving to and from areas will respawn the enemies every time, and if you are playing without swords, that may be a issue since Archers and Mages will have hard time to kill enemies after you level a little (the enemies also level with you), since the skills available are weak and useless bc they almost dont do damage(the moment you try the OP swords, anything else is a waste of effort).Secret of Magia still is interesting Action RPG game, and for its price, it does deliver, but it also true that, there are better options here on steam on that regard, unless you are in the RPG theme and enjoy little adventures from time to time, you wouldnt like the experience otherise."
